They are raised and processed in a humane manner, and are never adulterated in any way.  We want to make people's lives better, period. From the farmers raising our flocks, the chickens themselves, to the truck drivers delivering them, every single employee here at Common Wealth Poultry, to you - we want to tremendously impact lives in a huge way. It's why we do business in the pure, honest, and fresh way.  When you shop with us, your dollar is supporting a small family owned business in Maine. Your dollar supports the hard working artisan butchers we employ and their families, and every farmer who wakes up with the sun to genuinely care for the flocks. Your purchase here contributes to a greater purpose. When you shop with us, you too positively impact the lives of many people. Together, we can contribute to the commonwealth of all kinds.

CAN I EAT SWEET DOE GELATO IF I'M LACTOSE INTOLERANT?        This is the question we are probably asked more often than any other. The short answer is: ask your doctor! But
custitem_ns_sc_ext_id_hide_qty_avl: we're happy to share what we've learned through our own research and experience.        There appear to be many people who have been diagnosed as "lactose intolerant"" without every truly being tested for intolerance to lactose. More often
usecomponentyield: the intolerance is associated with a specific Casein protein found in cow's milk that is not present in goat's milk. As a result
custitem_commodity_code: many people have found that they can enjoy goat milk products
yahooproductfeed: without experiencing any of the symptoms typically associated with their consumption of products made with cow's milk. In fact
upccode: we've had lots of customers who are highly sensitive to cow dairy tell us
custitem_fc_zen_itemiscatchweight: that Sweet Doe Gelato is perfectly fine for them!        That said
itemtype: so if you are truly lactose intolerant and have been tested by your doctor to confirm it  then you should likely avoid dairy of all types.""

storedetaileddescription: Momo sauce is a handmade Himalayan style hot sauce. It is a tomato-based sauce made from our special family recipe that can be used as a dipping sauce or cooking sauce. This versatile sauce can be enjoyed with omelets, sandwiches, pizza, hot dogs, chicken wings, burgers, stir-fry, curries, lentils, soups, or on any other meals to add delicious Himalayan style spicy taste without overpowering the flavor. Momo sauce comes in 3 different flavors, Mild, Hot and Sesame, They are vegan and gluten free. It is made with simple, natural and traditional Himalayan ingredients including Coriander, Turmeric, Cumin, Cinnamon, Clove, ginger and garlic which will add Himalayan style spicy flavor to any meal or snack!

displayname: Sherpa Foods / Momos, Beef (Nepalese Dumplings) / Case, 8 retail packs
custitem6: SHE004 Sherpa Foods / Momos, Beef (Nepalese Dumplings) / Case, 8 retail packs
storedetaileddescription: This item is shipped frozen and can be slacked-out for refrigerated sales or sold frozen.        Momos are the Nepalese version of dumplings. It is thickly wrapped in flour dough with flavorful fillings of minced meats and vegetables served steamed or fried. It is comfort food made during special gatherings for guests.         Momos are pre-cooked.Reheat in microwave for 1-2 minutes or in nonstick pan for 5-8 minutes. Instruction for reheating in Microwave: Take Momos out of packaging and place in microwaveable container. Place in microwave and reheat for 1-2 minutes.Dip momos in momo sauce and enjoy. Instruction for heating in Frying Pan: Pour 3 Tbsp of vegetable oil into a nonstick pan. Take Momos out of packaging and place onto the pan. Heat on medium-high for 5-8 minutes turning each side every 2-3 minutes until all sides are golden brown or as preferred. Dip momos in momo sauce and enjoy.Recommended eating warm for better taste. Use caution handling or eating hot Momos.  Ingredients: Nepalese dumplings with mild momo sauce (Himalayan style hot sauce). Momo: unbleached hard wheat enriched flour ground beef, onion, salt, curry powder (natural color natural flavor), and vegetable oil. Momo sauce: tomato puree, water, onion, oil, dried red pepper, ginger, garlic, curry powder, coriander powder, salt.
description: Sherpa Foods / Momos, Beef (Nepalese Dumplings) / Case, 8 retail packs
purchasedescription: Momos, Beef (Nepalese Dumplings) / Case, 8 retail packs

storedetaileddescription:
Renaissance Ricotta: Heated in a steam kettle then hand-dipped into traditional tins, our Renaissance Ricotta can be enjoyed savory or sweet. This cheese has won many awards and once you taste it, you'll know why.

At Narragansett Creamery, we make cheese everyday because we love to and because we believe in freshness. We use local milk, kind bacteria, vegetable-based rennet, salt and nothing else. While we are not certified organic, we are thoughtful in our actions and our purchases. We support fair-trade and local ingredients to the best of our ability and our farmers pledge to not use growth hormones. We are proud to be a family-owned company supported by the Southern New England community we belong to.

storedetaileddescription: Raspberry Lime Made with Organic Raspberries and Limes The perfect blend of sweet and tangy.  It is the classic flavor combination with the added health benefits of kombucha.  Artisan Beverage Cooperative was founded in 2013 by the owners of Katalyst Kombucha LLC and Green River Ambrosia LLC. Katalyst Kombucha had been producing kombucha teas since 2005 in Greenfield, Massachusetts, and Green River Ambrosia began producing meads and Ginger Libation at the Katalyst brewery in 2007. After a few years of working together, the owners decided to merge the companies and convert the two businesses into a worker-owned cooperative. Both Katalyst Kombucha and Green River Ambrosia were founded on strong missions to promote environmental stewardship, democratic governance, sustainable agriculture, and building a strong local economy. As each company developed independently it became clear that by fully joining forces the mission of each company could be fulfilled more effectively and all of the operations could become much more efficient.

storedisplayname: Kitchen Garden Farm / Sriracha, Habanero, OG / Case, 12 x 8oz bottles
displayname: Kitchen Garden Farm / Sriracha, Habanero, OG / Case, 12 x 8oz bottles
custitem6: KGF005 Kitchen Garden Farm / Sriracha, Habanero, OG / Case, 12 x 8oz bottles
storedetaileddescription: Made from a mix of habanero and sweet orange peppers we grow on our farm in Sunderland, MA. The chilies are fermented for seven days, then cooked and pureed. Certified organic!  Farmer Made. No Preservatives. Certified Organic.    Our sriracha is a naturally fermented Asian-style chili sauce made from organic peppers grown here at the farm. It has a bright, fruity taste with sharp chili heat and a pronounced garlic flavor. It's delicious on eggs, rice, noodles, in soup, on grilled meats and fish and fried chicken. Kitchen Garden Farm Sriracha comes in 3 varieties: original, extra-hot habanero and super-hot ghost pepper. You can shop online, find us in stores or contact us for wholesale options.        Our Sriracha Is Handcrafted.    We start by selecting fully ripe organic peppers from our fields, which we grind with organic garlic, sugar and salt and allow to ferment for 4-10 days depending on the ambient temperature. After fermentation, the pepper mash" is heated and passed through a food mill to remove all of the skins and seeds. Then we cook it with vinegar and bottle it. Our sriracha sauce is sealed and shelf-stable but should be refrigerated after opening."
description: Kitchen Garden Farm / Sriracha, Habanero, OG / Case, 12 x 8oz bottles
custitem_fc_ingredients: Ingredients: Organic peppers, organic vinegar, organic cane sugar, organic garlic, sea salt, xanthan gum.
purchasedescription: Sriracha, Habanero, OG / Case, 12 x 8oz bottles

We aim to elevate the industry entirely.   Our animals are fed a diet that is 100% vegetarian and are not given growth promoting antibiotics. They are raised and processed in a humane manner, and are never adulterated in any way.  We want to make people's lives better, period. From the farmers raising our flocks, the chickens themselves, to the truck drivers delivering them, every single employee here at Common Wealth Poultry, to you - we want to tremendously impact lives in a huge way. It's why we do business in the pure, honest, and fresh way.  When you shop with us, your dollar is supporting a small family owned business in Maine. Your dollar supports the hard working artisan butchers we employ and their families, and every farmer who wakes up with the sun to genuinely care for the flocks. Your purchase here contributes to a greater purpose. When you shop with us, you too positively impact the lives of many people. Together, we can contribute to the commonwealth of all kinds.

It is shelf stable, and makes a great gift. It pours like maple syrup (not stiff like honey) Use it for making salad dressings, on ice cream, in mixed drinks (makes a fantastic hot toddy!), or with seltzer for a home made turmeric-ale! Be creative and be careful - it's addictive!        We have pioneered growing ginger and turmeric in the Northeast and are excited to offer this delicious, locally grown and made product. It's the only turmeric product out there made with local turmeric from the Northeast!        Produced ourselves in a Certified Organic kitchen (Franklin County Food Processing Center) in Greenfield, MA        Limited supply - very small batches...

displayname: Grafton Village Cheese / 1-Year Cheddar / Case, 12 x 4oz retail packs, wax
custitem6: GVC021 Grafton Village Cheese / 1-Year Cheddar / Case, 12 x 4oz retail packs, wax
storedetaileddescription:
A younger version of our flagship cheddar, aged for one full year to achieve the classic New England cheddar profile: comforting, lightly tangy, and rich. When determining which batches to age for 1 Year Cheddar, we look for slightly creamier textures and sweeter flavors that are best showcased in a relatively young cheese.

With an aroma of butter and fresh grass, our 1 Year Cheddar is mellow yet balanced, with aromas of fresh apples and butter. Flavors start off bright and lemony, evolving into a rich and nutty finish that is both comforting and satisfying.

This is a pleasant and mild table cheese; try it paired with fresh grapes or sliced fresh apples for a juicy counterpoint to its rich and buttery flavors. 1 Year Cheddar is also perfect for melting. Flavors becomes milder when melted, so mix with stronger cheeses to add character to a dish, if desired.
description: Grafton Village Cheese / 1-Year Cheddar / Case, 12 x 4oz retail packs, wax
custitem_fc_ingredients: Unpasteurized cow milk, salt, cultures, enzymes

storedetaileddescription:
Unpasteurized, Gluten-free, 4% acidity. 

About the Apple Balsamic Vinegar of Vermont
 
 
 
 Our Apple Balsamic Vinegar of Vermont (TM) is made from dozens of our own apple varieties, both tame and wild.
 
 
 
 The resulting cider vinegar is sweetened slightly with reduced organic cider. We add no other sugars or colorants. 
 
 
 
 Before bottling, we age and mellow our Apple Balsamic for over a year. Time and handmade barrles with five different woods contribute to its fine flavor.
 
 
 
 Use as you would any other balsamic: as a drizzle, in marinades and glazes, and for a unique twist on a classic and delicious vinagrette.

displayname: Rhapsody Natural Foods / Natto, Small Bean, Non-GMO / Case, 12 x 3.5oz retail tubs
custitem6: RHA005 Rhapsody Natural Foods / Natto, Small Bean, Non-GMO / Case, 12 x 3.5oz retail tubs
storedetaileddescription: Natto, sticky fermented whole soybeans, is a traditional Japanese breakfast food. It is the richest food source of vitamin K2 (1000 mcg per 100 grams or 3.5 oz), essential in proper calcium absorption. Natto is also a living food and contains the highly beneficial probiotic enzyme nattokinase. Nattokinase is key in a healthy digestive system, known to aid in digestive disorders, especially those caused by antibiotic use, and essential for proper blood clotting mechanisms.        Rhapsody Natto comes in two varieties: large bean (organic) & small bean (non-gmo). Our natto containers are 100% compostable in a commercial facility and the paper cups are made without cutting down trees (sugarcane paper with corn-based lining).
description: Rhapsody Natural Foods / Natto, Small Bean, Non-GMO / Case, 12 x 3.5oz retail tubs
custitem_fc_ingredients: Non-GMO soybeans, well water, Bacillus subtillus culture.

storedetaileddescription: Since 1870 six generations of the Robie Family have worked this 150 acre farm situated on the Connecticut River in Piermont, NH.  Pasture Poultry are raised in movable pens in our pastures from May through October.  The chickens and turkeys are processed here on the farm and sold in the farm store. Pigs are also part of the barnyard animals that are raised on the farm.  Though not in great number, they provide excellent pork products that are also sold in the farm store. A Greenhouse was constructed in the fall of 2020 which will provide many opportunities to expand our ability to diversify even further.    We are dedicated to learning and implementing new farming advancements and technology which will contribute to our success both now and in the future, while, at the same time, being committed to sustaining the land through conservation and ecological measures.

Ingredients 100% pasture-raised pork, water, uncured bacon (pork belly, sea salt), sea salt, organic dextrose from tapioca (used to initiate fermentation), celery juice powder, organic jalapeno powder, organic jalapeno pieces, organic black pepper, lactic acid starter culture, stuffed in a dye-free collagen casing. storedisplayname: Hall Apiaries / Raw Honey / 60# bulk pail
displayname: Hall Apiaries / Raw Honey / 60# bulk pail
custitem6: HAL001 Hall Apiaries / Raw Honey / 60# bulk pail
storedetaileddescription: Harvested from only Hall Apiaries hives in the Upper Valley of VT and NH.             All honey is unheated / raw, gravity filtered to retain all the natural enzymes, aroma and flavor profile that honey is meant to be. Being that the honey is raw, crystallization will take place and is a natural process. To bring the honey back to a liquid state simply place the container in a water bath at 80 - 90 degrees until liquid.            Light amber- Collected by the bees from May - August. Most of the nectar profile in this honey is derived from basswood (linden) blossoms. Other nectar sources include clovers, black locust, dandelion, honey suckle, sumac and milkweed.            Dark amber- Collected by the bees from mid August - early September. Nectar profiles in this honey vary from year to year but are mainly made up of golden rod, Japanese knot-weed, and asters. This honey will crystallize quickly!
description: Hall Apiaries / Raw Honey / 60# bulk pail
purchasedescription: Raw Honey / 60# bulk pail

custitem6: RHA004 Rhapsody Natural Foods / Natto, Large Bean, OG / Case, 12 x 3.5oz retail tubs
storedetaileddescription: Natto, sticky fermented whole soybeans, is a traditional Japanese breakfast food. It is the richest food source of vitamin K2 (1000 mcg per 100 grams or 3.5 oz), essential in proper calcium absorption. Natto is also a living food and contains the highly beneficial probiotic enzyme nattokinase. Nattokinase is key in a healthy digestive system, known to aid in digestive disorders, especially those caused by antibiotic use, and essential for proper blood clotting mechanisms.    Rhapsody Natto comes in two varieties: large bean (organic) & small bean (non-gmo). Our natto containers are 100% compostable in a commercial facility and the paper cups are made without cutting down trees (sugarcane paper with corn-based lining).

custitem6: KAT017 Katalyst Kombucha / Hopped Katalyst Kombucha / Bulk, keg, 5.2 gallons
storedetaileddescription: Hopped Taste the tropical citrus aromas and flavors of hops without the bitterness or the buzz.  Forget beer, drink hopped kombucha instead!  Artisan Beverage Cooperative was founded in 2013 by the owners of Katalyst Kombucha LLC and Green River Ambrosia LLC. Katalyst Kombucha had been producing kombucha teas since 2005 in Greenfield, Massachusetts, and Green River Ambrosia began producing meads and Ginger Libation at the Katalyst brewery in 2007. After a few years of working together, the owners decided to merge the companies and convert the two businesses into a worker-owned cooperative. Both Katalyst Kombucha and Green River Ambrosia were founded on strong missions to promote environmental stewardship, democratic governance, sustainable agriculture, and building a strong local economy. As each company developed independently it became clear that by fully joining forces the mission of each company could be fulfilled more effectively and all of the operations could become much more efficient.
description: Katalyst Kombucha / Hopped Katalyst Kombucha / Bulk, keg, 5.2 gallons

storedisplayname: Kitchen Garden Farm / Sriracha, Original, OG / Case, 12 x 8oz bottles
displayname: Kitchen Garden Farm / Sriracha, Original, OG / Case, 12 x 8oz bottles
custitem6: KGF006 Kitchen Garden Farm / Sriracha, Original, OG / Case, 12 x 8oz bottles
storedetaileddescription: Made from several kinds of red chilies grown here on our farm in Sunderland, MA. The chilies are fermented for seven days, then cooked and pureed. Compared with other sriracha it has an incredibly fresh fruity pepper flavor. Certified organic!  Farmer Made. No Preservatives. Certified Organic.    Our sriracha is a naturally fermented Asian-style chili sauce made from organic peppers grown here at the farm. It has a bright, fruity taste with sharp chili heat and a pronounced garlic flavor. It's delicious on eggs, rice, noodles, in soup, on grilled meats and fish and fried chicken. Kitchen Garden Farm Sriracha comes in 3 varieties: original, extra-hot habanero and super-hot ghost pepper. You can shop online, find us in stores or contact us for wholesale options.    Our Sriracha Is Handcrafted.    We start by selecting fully ripe organic peppers from our fields, which we grind with organic garlic, sugar and salt and allow to ferment for 4-10 days depending on the ambient temperature. After fermentation, the pepper mash" is heated and passed through a food mill to remove all of the skins and seeds. Then we cook it with vinegar and bottle it. Our sriracha sauce is sealed and shelf-stable but should be refrigerated after opening."
description: Kitchen Garden Farm / Sriracha, Original, OG / Case, 12 x 8oz bottles
custitem_fc_ingredients: Ingredients: Organic chilies, organic vinegar, organic cane sugar, organic garlic, sea salt, xanthan gum.

storedetaileddescription: Certified Organic Dried Cranberries from Fairland Farms / Cape Cod Organic Cranberry        12 x 8 oz retail packages  Fairland Farm, LLC and Cape Cod Organic Cranberry, LLC were formed to become stewards of the continuing agricultural history of Southeastern Massachusetts and Cape Cod. Numerous communities of this culturally important area are impacted by the use of Best Management Practices which Fairland Farm prides itself on. Some of the bogs that have been placed in our care have existed prior to the Civil War. Not only are we mindful to the benefits to the food industry from the growing of cranberries but we are daily reminded that the surrounding support land, whether it be upland or lowland, is a significant resource for the various plants and animals that exist within our borders.Our cranberry products can be found in most of the five star restaurants in Rhode Island and in many grocery stores who feature local products including Whole Foods.

custitem6: ROB001 Robie Farm / Ground Pork, Frozen / Case, 12 x 1# retail packs
storedetaileddescription: Since 1870 six generations of the Robie Family have worked this 150 acre farm situated on the Connecticut River in Piermont, NH.  Pasture Poultry are raised in movable pens in our pastures from May through October.  The chickens and turkeys are processed here on the farm and sold in the farm store. Pigs are also part of the barnyard animals that are raised on the farm.  Though not in great number, they provide excellent pork products that are also sold in the farm store. A Greenhouse was constructed in the fall of 2020 which will provide many opportunities to expand our ability to diversify even further.   We are dedicated to learning and implementing new farming advancements and technology which will contribute to our success both now and in the future, while, at the same time, being committed to sustaining the land through conservation and ecological measures.

vendorname: Wine Vinegar, Better than Champagne Chardonnay
storedetaileddescription: Made with chardonnay from California this vinegar would be a blanc and blancs if it were a champagne. Luckily it is not, it is better. It is slow fermented in small batches using a unique process from the early 1800s and aged in 25-gallon American oak barrels.        Our Better Than Champagne Vinegar is just that. It is not champagne vinegar, it is its' better cousin from across the pond and we couldn't be happier with how this little upstart turned out.        Naming Note: Why don't we call it Champagne vinegar? We told you- it's better... AND we strive to make vinegars with a sense of place and that respect that sense of place in other foods. Champagne vinegar should come from the Champagne region of France. Our vinegar is made from traditional champagne grapes (ie chardonnay) but it is made in our vinegar works in New England, not France. This beautiful vinegar reflects the American wine tradition and builds on champagne-inspired vinegar flavor profiles.
description: American Vinegar Works / Wine Vinegar, Better than Champagne Chardonnay / Case, 6 x 250ml

storedisplayname: Blank Slate Kitchen / Zhug / Case, 12 x 6oz jars
displayname: Blank Slate Kitchen / Zhug / Case, 12 x 6oz jars
custitem6: BLN002 Blank Slate Kitchen / Zhug / Case, 12 x 6oz jars
storedetaileddescription:
Zhug is a bright, herby, spicy and versatile condiment originally from Yemen and popular throughout the Middle East. A blend of chopped jalapenos, cilantro, parsley, garlic, lemon juice and olive oil, and seasoned with salt, black pepper, cumin and cardamom, if you're not familiar with it yet, you could think of it as a Middle Eastern chimichurri. This general purpose condiment has a bold, spicy flavor that is both hot and tangy, aromatic and herbaceous and brings a savory, rich punch to anything you put it on.

You can use your Zhug as a condiment on almost anything. It is particularly well-suited for Middle Eastern foods such as shawarma, falafel, hummus, and grilled lamb. It is also great on any savory Western dishes as well, such as fish, chicken, beef, as a dip by itself or mixed with yogurt or mayo, as a sandwich spread, or as a marinade.
description: Blank Slate Kitchen / Zhug / Case, 12 x 6oz jars
custitem_fc_ingredients: jalapeno, cilantro, parsley, lemon juice, garlic, olive oil, salt, black pepper, cumin, cardamon

custitem6: SPA017_SP Singing Pastures / Roam Sticks, Variety Pack / Small case, 8 x 6ct display boxes
storedetaileddescription:
Who says we can't have it all? This ultimate sampler pack gives you six crave-quenching hickory-smoked pork sticks, two of each flavor: uncured bacon, pineapple, and jalapeno.

Hickory-smoked Pork with Uncured Bacon Ingredients: 100% pasture-raised pork, water, sea salt, uncured bacon - no nitrates or nitrites added* (pork, water, sea salt), organic dextrose (made from tapioca), celery juice powder, pepper, lactic acid starter culture, in a beef collagen casing. 
 
 Hickory-smoked Pork with Pineapple Ingredients: 100% pasture-raised pork, water, sea salt, dried pineapple (pineapple, sugar), non-GMO dextrose (made from tapioca), celery juice powder, pepper, lactic acid starter culture, in a beef collagen casing.

storedetaileddescription: Shelf-Stable.  A HOT MESS of a salami: when we were still getting our sea legs over at the new plant, we did a silly thing, you see. We made a big batch of our Classic Salami (one of the mildest flavors we make) and accidentally added three times the amount of crushed chili flake that was supposed to go in there. The result was good -- better than good even! -- but definitely was ....... curiously spicy. And so, Hot Mess, A Curiously Spicy Salami, was born! The mystery of its origin was eventually unraveled and now its future is up to you: will this be the sole batch ever to grace our imperfect world, or will it take its rightful place alongside its brothers and sisters in the Short Creek salami pantheon? Speak, and be heard!

custitem6: KAT001 Katalyst Kombucha / Bliss Berry Kombucha, OG / Case, 12 x 16oz bottles
storedetaileddescription: Artisan Beverage Cooperative was founded in 2013 by the owners of Katalyst Kombucha LLC and Green River Ambrosia LLC. Katalyst Kombucha had been producing kombucha teas since 2005 in Greenfield, Massachusetts, and Green River Ambrosia began producing meads and Ginger Libation at the Katalyst brewery in 2007. After a few years of working together, the owners decided to merge the companies and convert the two businesses into a worker-owned cooperative. Both Katalyst Kombucha and Green River Ambrosia were founded on strong missions to promote environmental stewardship, democratic governance, sustainable agriculture, and building a strong local economy. As each company developed independently it became clear that by fully joining forces the mission of each company could be fulfilled more effectively and all of the operations could become much more efficient.
description: Katalyst Kombucha / Bliss Berry Kombucha, OG / Case, 12 x 16oz bottles

This versatile sauce can be enjoyed with omelets, sandwiches, pizza, hot dogs, chicken wings, burgers, stir-fry, curries, lentils, soups, or on any other meals to add delicious Himalayan style spicy taste without overpowering the flavor. custitem6: SHE005 Sherpa Foods / Momos, Chicken (Nepalese Dumplings) / Case, 8 retail packs
storedetaileddescription: This item is shipped frozen and can be slacked-out for refrigerated sales or sold frozen.    Momos are the Nepalese version of dumplings. It is thickly wrapped in flour dough with flavorful fillings of minced meats and vegetables served steamed or fried. It is comfort food made during special gatherings for guests.         Momos are pre-cooked.Reheat in microwave for 1-2 minutes or in nonstick pan for 5-8 minutes. Instruction for reheating in Microwave: Take Momos out of packaging and place in microwaveable container. Place in microwave and reheat for 1-2 minutes.Dip momos in momo sauce and enjoy. Instruction for heating in Frying Pan: Pour 3 Tbsp of vegetable oil into a nonstick pan. Take Momos out of packaging and place onto the pan. Heat on medium-high for 5-8 minutes turning each side every 2-3 minutes until all sides are golden brown or as preferred. Dip momos in momo sauce and enjoy.Recommended eating warm for better taste. Use caution handling or eating hot Momos.  Ingredients: Nepalese dumplings with mild momo sauce (Himalayan style hot sauce). Momo: unbleached hard wheat enriched flour ground chicken, onion, salt, curry powder (natural color natural flavor), and vegetable oil. Momo sauce: tomato puree, water, onion, oil, dried red pepper, ginger, garlic, curry powder, coriander powder, salt.
description: Sherpa Foods / Momos, Chicken (Nepalese Dumplings) / Case, 8 retail packs
purchasedescription: Momos, Chicken (Nepalese Dumplings) / Case, 8 retail packs

storedetaileddescription: Who says we can't have it all? Hickory-smoked Pork with Uncured Bacon Ingredients: 100% pasture-raised pork, water, sea salt, uncured bacon - no nitrates or nitrites added* (pork, water, sea salt), organic dextrose (made from tapioca), celery juice powder, pepper, lactic acid starter culture, in a beef collagen casing.             Hickory-smoked Pork with Pineapple Ingredients: 100% pasture-raised pork, water, sea salt, dried pineapple (pineapple, sugar), non-GMO dextrose (made from tapioca), celery juice powder, pepper, lactic acid starter culture, in a beef collagen casing.            Hickory-smoked Pork with Jalapeno Ingredients: 100% pasture-raised pork, water, uncured bacon (pork belly, sea salt), sea salt, organic dextrose from tapioca (used to initiate fermentation), celery juice powder, organic jalapeno powder, organic jalapeno pieces, organic black pepper, lactic acid starter culture, stuffed in a dye-free collagen casing. No nitrates or nitrites added except for those naturally occurring in sea salt and celery juice powder.

storedisplayname: Hall Apiaries / Raw Honey / Bulk, 24#, 2 gallons
displayname: Hall Apiaries / Raw Honey / Bulk, 24#, 2 gallons
custitem6: HAL007 Hall Apiaries / Raw Honey / Bulk, 24#, 2 gallons
storedetaileddescription: Harvested from only Hall Apiaries hives in the Upper Valley of VT and NH.  All honey is unheated / raw, gravity filtered to retain all the natural enzymes, aroma and flavor profile that honey is meant to be. Being that the honey is raw, crystallization will take place and is a natural process. To bring the honey back to a liquid state simply place the container in a water bath at 80 - 90 degrees until liquid.  Light amber- Collected by the bees from May - August. Most of the nectar profile in this honey is derived from basswood (linden) blossoms. Other nectar sources include clovers, black locust, dandelion, honey suckle, sumac and milkweed. Dark amber- Collected by the bees from mid August - early September. Nectar profiles in this honey vary from year to year but are mainly made up of golden rod, Japanese knot-weed, and asters. This honey will crystallize quickly!
description: Hall Apiaries / Raw Honey / Bulk, 24#, 2 gallons
purchasedescription: Raw Honey / Bulk, 24#, 2 gallons

custitem6: KAT006 Katalyst Kombucha / Ginger Devotion Kombucha, OG / Case, 24 x 12 oz cans
storedetaileddescription: Artisan Beverage Cooperative was founded in 2013 by the owners of Katalyst Kombucha LLC and Green River Ambrosia LLC. Katalyst Kombucha had been producing kombucha teas since 2005 in Greenfield, Massachusetts, and Green River Ambrosia began producing meads and Ginger Libation at the Katalyst brewery in 2007. After a few years of working together, the owners decided to merge the companies and convert the two businesses into a worker-owned cooperative. Both Katalyst Kombucha and Green River Ambrosia were founded on strong missions to promote environmental stewardship, democratic governance, sustainable agriculture, and building a strong local economy. As each company developed independently it became clear that by fully joining forces the mission of each company could be fulfilled more effectively and all of the operations could become much more efficient.
description: Katalyst Kombucha / Ginger Devotion Kombucha, OG / Case, 24 x 12 oz cans
purchasedescription: Ginger Devotion Kombucha, OG / Case, 24 x 12 oz cans

displayname: Hall Apiaries / Raw Honey / Case, 12 x 16oz retail jars
custitem6: HAL002 Hall Apiaries / Raw Honey / Case, 12 x 16oz retail jars
storedetaileddescription: Harvested from only Hall Apiaries hives in the Upper Valley of VT and NH.             All honey is unheated / raw, gravity filtered to retain all the natural enzymes, aroma and flavor profile that honey is meant to be. Being that the honey is raw, crystallization will take place and is a natural process. To bring the honey back to a liquid state simply place the container in a water bath at 80 - 90 degrees until liquid.            Light amber- Collected by the bees from May - August. Most of the nectar profile in this honey is derived from basswood (linden) blossoms. Other nectar sources include clovers, black locust, dandelion, honey suckle, sumac and milkweed.            Dark amber- Collected by the bees from mid August - early September. Nectar profiles in this honey vary from year to year but are mainly made up of golden rod, Japanese knot-weed, and asters. This honey will crystallize quickly!
description: Hall Apiaries / Raw Honey / Case, 12 x 16oz retail jars
